Problem Statement-
A tiny creative studio has 3 computers and 1 central network storage server (FTP).
They just bought an unmanaged switch and want to make sure every computer can manually
assign an address, talk to each other, and transfer files to the storage server without any internet.

Devices used-
an unmanaged router
3 pc
server

what we did-
server was connected to fa 1
pc 3 , 4 and 5 were connected to fa 2,3,4 respectively ,
it specifically asked for manual assigment of ipv4 address so we just  assigned static
ipv4 address , server was assigned 192.168.1.1
pc 3,4,5 were given 192.168.1.2 , 192.168.1.3 and 192.168.1.4 respectively.

then all was left was to configure FTP,
we created 3 accounts to access the server for each pc
for eg- for pc3 we had 
  username= pc3
  password= pc3@123

just like this we have for pc 4 and 5 also
